  "doc_id": "24030",
  "text": "Hemorrhage during orthotopic liver transplantation (OLT) is relatively easy to detect and treat. Thrombosis, however, is frequently unexpected and more difficult to detect before hemodynamic instability occurs. Recent evidence suggests that the occurrence of intracardiac thrombosis (ICT) during OLT is not as rare as was once thought. [CITATION_1] The majority of cases occur shortly after reperfusion, 2 a period also associated with enhanced fibrinolysis. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] We therefore pose the question of how to treat a patient that suffers both an ICT and significant hyperfibrinolysis? A case of an OLT with a hemodynamically significant ICT and subsequent hyperfibrinolysis with massive blood loss is presented.",
